11/05/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Interior Minister Igli Toska said in an interview with the BBC on Monday (10 May) that fighting organised crime, corruption and money laundering were among the government's main priorities. 
Toska, who is visiting the UK, said co-operation in this field was the focus of his talks with British officials. 
He added that Albania plans to establish a police attach√© position in London to co-ordinate joint efforts against organised crime and illegal trafficking. 
(ATA, BBC - 10/05/04)
